article.headline: Ohio 91, Toledo 58
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- Jerome Tillman scored 25 points and Justin Orr came off the bench to lead Ohio's sharpshooting from behind the arc in a 91-58 victory over Toledo on Saturday. Tillman hit 10-of-14 shots from the field and also had seven rebounds and two assists as the Bobcats (13-11, 6-5) rolled to a 39-29 lead at the half and never looked back. They hit 61 percent of their shots from the field (31 of 51), including shooting at a 71 percent clip in the second half. Orr hit 5-of-6 3-pointers while scoring 19 points as Ohio finished hit a season-high 14 shots behind the arc in 23 attempts. Steve Coleman added 13 points and Michael Allen 11 for the Bobcats, who have won 24 of their last 26 home games. Jonathan Amos didn't start but scored 32 points for Toledo (4-21, 2-9). Ridley Johnson chipped in with 11 for the Rockets, who never led.
